This article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama declaring March 2015 as Women's History Month. The proclamation acknowledges the contributions of women throughout history in fighting for equality and justice. It highlights the progress made in terms of women's participation in the workforce and calls for equal pay for equal work, workplace flexibility, access to paid leave, and quality childcare. The proclamation emphasizes that women's issues are not just women's issues but also family issues and national economic priorities. It concludes by urging Americans to celebrate Women's History Month and International Women's Day and to learn more about the impact of women in history.